onne-319x300.jpg" class="webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin: auto;margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%" /><p>Sur invitation de la Chambre de Commerce et d&#8217;Industrie de Bayonne, j&#8217;ai eu le plaisir d&#8217;animer une conférence fleuve de 3H intitulée WordPress Labs. Retrouvez les slides de mon intervention et le résumé de ma présentation dans ce billet. L&#8217;intervention s&#8217;est déroulée en 3 temps : Une première partie de présentation générale sur WordPress (histoire, points forts [&#8230;]</p>\n<p></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/su6pjoP-9jw" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://wpchannel.com/conference-meilleur-site-wordpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:104:"A busy week ahead of us – today we’re releasing reserved tickets; schedule to be published on Friday";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/rechJ-wJmQQ/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:141:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/05/02/a-busy-week-ahead-of-us-today-were-releasing-reserved-tickets-schedule-to-be-published-on-friday/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 02 May 2017 13:48:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:382:"\n		        This week is one of the busiest leading to WordCamp Europe. As of today, we have sold 2100 tickets and this week we&#8217;ll release the rest of the reserved tickets to bring us to the magical number of 3000 attendees. &#8230; Continue reading A busy week ahead of us – today we&#8217;re releasing reserved tickets; schedule to be published on Friday  &#8594;		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"WordCamp Europe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3238:"<div id="attachment_5190" style="width: 1410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="wp-image-5190 size-full" src="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/files/2017/05/reserved-tickets-1.jpg" alt="" width="1400" height="800" /><p class="wp-caption-text">We are releasing all reserved (but unclaimed) tickets today; and plan to publish final schedule on Friday</p></div>\n<p>This week is one of the busiest leading to WordCamp Europe. As of today, <strong>we have sold 2100 tickets</strong> and this week we&#8217;ll release the<strong> rest of the reserved tickets to bring us to the magical number of 3000 attendees</strong>. But not only that – you often asked us &#8220;when will you publish the schedule?&#8221; Well, your wait is (almost) over. We&#8217;re happy to say that the <strong>final schedule will be announced this week</strong> – as soon as we finish rolling out speaker announcements.</p>\n<p><span id="more-5157"></span></p>\n<h2>Releasing 670 reserved tickets</h2>\n<p>We released the first batch of tickets after the closing remarks in Vienna and the final batch in February. As of today <strong>we have sold 2100 tickets</strong>, which is absolutely fantastic! With that, a month and a half before the event, we have <strong>surpassed the number of attendees we had in Vienna</strong>.</p>\n<p>As WordCamp Europe grows, we aim not only for more attendees but for more speakers, volunteers and sponsors as well. To make sure everyone will be able to attend before we even start releasing tickets, we have to <strong>reserve some of the tickets for speakers</strong> (both those selected and those rejected), <strong>volunteers and sponsors</strong>. And we did reserve a fair amount for all of them.</p>\n<p>Luckily for us, quite a lot of sponsors, volunteers and sponsors already purchased their tickets the regular way, showing their love and support for the European community and WordCamp Europe. <strong>Today we are releasing those unclaimed tickets, making sure that everyone who wants to be in Paris – can be.</strong></p>\n<h2>Finishing the speaker announcements</h2>\n<p>We started rolling out <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speakers/">speaker</a> announcements almost a month ago. Speakers were arranged into thematic groups and we published two <a href="https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/tag/speakers/">announcements</a> per week. For this (final) week we are making an exception and we&#8217;ll be releasing <strong>three speaker announcements by the end of the week</strong>, with the first one published <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/05/02/seventh-group-of-wceu-speakers-k-adam-white-alain-schlesser-ivelina-dimova-dwayne-mcdaniel/">earlier today</a>.</p>\n<p>After the final announcement on Friday, <strong>we&#8217;ll publish the full schedule as well</strong>.</p>\n<h2>WordCamp Europe is (about) you</h2>\n<p>WordCamp Europe grows every year and this is possible thanks to people like you, who support us, who share our stories, values and optimism. <strong>Thank you for being here.</strong> Thank you for being with us on a journey that will result in the biggest WordCamp ever.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/rechJ-wJmQQ" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:141:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/05/02/a-busy-week-ahead-of-us-today-were-releasing-reserved-tickets-schedule-to-be-published-on-friday/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:117:"Seventh Group of #WCEU speakers – K. Adam White, Alain Schlesser, Ivelina Dimova, Dwayne McDaniel, and Andrew Nacin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/VQ6CTluJxPg/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:135:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/05/02/seventh-group-of-wceu-speakers-k-adam-white-alain-schlesser-ivelina-dimova-dwayne-mcdaniel/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 02 May 2017 08:58:34 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:428:"\n		        We&#8217;re proud to present our next group of technical talks to you. Please, extend our welcome to K. Adam White, Alain Schlesser, Ivelina Dimova, Dwayne McDaniel, and Andrew Nacin. They will cover development topics ranging from REST API to development &#8230; Continue reading Seventh Group of #WCEU speakers – K. Adam White, Alain Schlesser, Ivelina Dimova, Dwayne McDaniel, and Andrew Nacin  &#8594;		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"WordCamp Europe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4933:"<div id="attachment_5168" style="width: 1410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-full wp-image-5168" src="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/files/2017/05/wceu-speakers-group-7.jpg" alt="" width="1400" height="800" /><p class="wp-caption-text">WordCamp Europe speakers – K. Adam White, Alain Schlesser, Ivelina Dimova, Dwayne McDaniel, and Andrew Nacin</p></div>\n<p>We&#8217;re proud to present our next group of technical talks to you. Please, extend our welcome to K. Adam White, Alain Schlesser, Ivelina Dimova, Dwayne McDaniel, and Andrew Nacin. They will cover development topics ranging from REST API to development best practices and tricks.</p>\n<p><span id="more-4757"></span></p>\n<h2>K. Adam White &#8211; Data Visualisation with the REST API</h2>\n<p>As an engineer at Bocoup, <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/k-adam-white/">K. Adam White</a> writes web applications, contributes to open-source projects, and evangelises the web as an open platform for technology and collaboration. His talk, &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/data-visualization-with-the-rest-api">Data Visualisation with the REST API</a>,&#8221; will explore how the REST API can be combined with visualisation tools like D3.js to gain new insights into your content. He&#8217;ll demonstrate how build a network diagram to visualize how tags and categories area applied to posts, then explain how to use custom post types and register_meta to build a completely custom dashboard within WordPress for any type of data.</p>\n<h2>Alain Schlesser &#8211; Demystifying the WordPress Bootstrap Process</h2>\n<p>The WordPress bootstrap process is only scarcely documented, with only a very select group of developers that truly know the ins and outs and historical reasons behind the individual bootstrapping steps. Want to know more? <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/alain-schlesser/">Alain</a>, a freelance software engineer and WordPress consultant, will be &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/demystifying-the-wordpress-bootstrap-process">Demystifying the WordPress Bootstrap Process</a>&#8221; at WordCamp Europe this summer. In his talk, Alain will present a detailed overview of the exact execution flow that launches your WordPress site on each page request and introduce a feature project that aims to improve the existing bootstrap process.</p>\n<h2>Ivelina Dimova &#8211; Make your own WP-CLI command in 10min</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/ivelina-dimova/">Ivelina</a> is a WordPress developer at CrowdFavorite who is focused on back-end development and passionate about version control systems, deployment and server administration tools. Many in the WordPress community benefit from WP-CLI, a management tool that can make your development flow a lot easier. Ever wondered how that tool can be extended to support custom commands? Ivelina will provide a short overview on just that in &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/make-your-own-wp-cli-command-in-10min">Make your own WP-CLI command in 10min</a>.&#8221;</p>\n<h2>Dwayne McDaniel &#8211; We Are All Making This Up: Improv Lessons For Developers</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/dwayne-mcdaniel/">Dwayne</a> is a Community and Agency Success Manager at Pantheon, a role in which he has had the privilege of presenting at multiple events. He will discuss the parallels between the open source development world and improv communities in his talk: &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/we-are-all-making-this-up-improv-lessons-for-developers">We Are All Making This Up: Improv Lessons For Developers</a>.&#8221; The talk will offer guidance on how you can directly apply the core principles from the stagecraft of improv to create better code, smoother projects, and happier customers.</p>\n<h2>Andrew Nacin</h2>\n<p>As lead developer of WordPress, <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/andrew-nacin/">Andrew</a> led major releases, mentored contributors, and spearheaded new development. He has strong feelings about the core philosophies of WordPress, among them “decisions, not options” — software should be opinionated in lieu of burdening the user with too many options.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Get your ticket today</h2>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already, don&#8217;t forget to get <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/tickets/">your WordCamp Europe ticket</a>. Your WordCamp Europe ticket covers both days of the conference &#8211; June 16 and 17th &#8211; and contributor day on Thursday, June 15th. It grants you <strong>access to all sessions, lunch, coffee breaks, and the after party</strong>. It also includes an exclusive #WCEU 2017 <strong>t-shirt, stickers, and other great swag</strong>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/VQ6CTluJxPg" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:135:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/05/02/seventh-group-of-wceu-speakers-k-adam-white-alain-schlesser-ivelina-dimova-dwayne-mcdaniel/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"WordPress :: Ajouter une image lightbox avant le titre dans Genesis";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/KNEXSLNigbU/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"https://www.gregoirenoyelle.com/wordpress-ajouter-image-lightbox-avant-titre-genesis/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 02 May 2017 04:30:51 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:553:"\n		        Dans cet article nous allons voir comment ajouter l&#8217;image à la une avant le titre de l&#8217;article. Celle-ci sera cliquable et l&#8217;effet lightbox sera donc possible si vous avez une extension qui génère ce type d&#8217;effet. Création du modèle pour les articles Dans cette partie nous verrons pourquoi et comment créer un modèle de page ...Cet article a été publié le 2 mai 2017 par Grégoire Noyelle. Pour le lire en ligne, suivre le lien: WordPress :: Ajouter une image lightbox avant le titre dans Genesis.		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:776:"Dans cet article nous allons voir comment ajouter l&#8217;image à la une avant le titre de l&#8217;article. Celle-ci sera cliquable et l&#8217;effet lightbox sera donc possible si vous avez une extension qui génère ce type d&#8217;effet. Création du modèle pour les articles Dans cette partie nous verrons pourquoi et comment créer un modèle de page ...<p>Cet article a été publié le 2 mai 2017 par <a href="https://www.gregoirenoyelle.com">Grégoire Noyelle</a>. Pour le lire en ligne, suivre le lien: <a href="https://www.gregoirenoyelle.com/wordpress-ajouter-image-lightbox-avant-titre-genesis/">WordPress :: Ajouter une image lightbox avant le titre dans Genesis</a>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/KNEXSLNigbU" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"https://www.gregoirenoyelle.com/wordpress-ajouter-image-lightbox-avant-titre-genesis/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"Connaissez-vous les clients toxiques ?";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/oKI17vUjK6s/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"https://wpformation.com/clients-toxiques/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 28 Apr 2017 16:25:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:526:"\n		        Nous connaissons tous le vieil adage "Le client est Roi", internetement parlant on pourrait en citer d''autres : "Le contenu est Roi", "Si Google le dit...", bref ce n''est pas ce qui manque. Nous savons également qu''ils ne sont pas toujours appropriés... Aujourd''hui je ne vais pas vous parler de WordPress mais de la relation [&#8230;]\n\n\nConnaissez-vous les clients toxiques ? est un article de WP Formation\nFormation WordPress &amp; WooCommerce - Pour ne rien manquer : Abonnez-vous à la newsletter !\n		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"WP Formation";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1250:"<p><img width="1000" height="564" src="https://wpformation.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/toxic-client.jpg" class="attachment-Large size-Large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-left: 0px;margin-right: auto;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;max-width: 640px;max-height: 400px" />Nous connaissons tous le vieil adage "Le client est Roi", internetement parlant on pourrait en citer d''autres : "Le contenu est Roi", "Si Google le dit...", bref ce n''est pas ce qui manque. Nous savons également qu''ils ne sont pas toujours appropriés... Aujourd''hui je ne vais pas vous parler de WordPress mais de la relation [&#8230;]</p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpformation.com/clients-toxiques/">Connaissez-vous les clients toxiques ?</a> est un article de <a title="Formation WordPress Ecommerce" href="https://wpformation.com">WP Formation</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://wpformation.com/formation-wordpress/">Formation WordPress</a> &amp; <a href="https://wpformation.com/formation-woocommerce-e-commerce/">WooCommerce</a> - Pour ne rien manquer : <a href="https://wpformation.com/abonnement-newsletter-wpf/">Abonnez-vous à la newsletter</a> !</p>\n<hr><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/oKI17vUjK6s" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"https://wpformation.com/clients-toxiques/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"Coworking Spaces Selection";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/xPR6p2UIgmk/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/04/28/coworking-spaces-selection/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 28 Apr 2017 15:46:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:170:"\n		        A selection of 6 parisian coworking spaces with discounted prices for WordCamp Europe attendees. Continue reading Coworking Spaces Selection  &#8594;		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"WordCamp Europe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3215:"<div id="attachment_4953" style="width: 1410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-full wp-image-4953" src="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/files/2017/04/coworking.jpg" alt="" width="1400" height="800" /><p class="wp-caption-text">List of coworking places in Paris with special WordCamp Europe discount</p></div>\n<p>This is the digital age. There are times when we all need a cosy place to work while we are travelling. It is not an easy task when you don&#8217;t know so much about the place you are visiting. Maybe you will need to find such places while attending the WordCamp Europe. Paris, as any other city, have numerous coworking spaces where you can rent<em> un chouette coin</em> (a sweet spot). So to get you covered, we have selected 6 coworking spaces for you and dealt discounted prices for WordCamp Europe attendees. <strong>You can show up in any of them, show your WCEU ticket and get a 20% discount.</strong><span id="more-4919"></span></p>\n<h2>Nuage Café</h2>\n<p>An inspiring working place and a quality coffee shop for innovators who need a good coffee and Wifi, ideally located in the 5th district of Paris.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>14 Rue des Carmes, 75005 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 9 82 39 80 69</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.nuagecafe.fr/">www.nuagecafe.fr</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>myCowork Montorgueil</h2>\n<p>A luminous and verdant coworking space with fresh homemade coffee and fiber. You can also rent a private office and meeting rooms.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>54 Rue Greneta, 75002 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 1 85 09 08 29</li>\n<li><a href="http://mycowork.fr/">mycowork.fr</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Le 10h10 Coworking Café &#8211; Clery</h2>\n<p>A warm and cosy place to work where you will feel at home among antiqued furnitures. Of course, we have food, drinks, coffee and Wifi for you.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>19 Rue de Cléry, 75002 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 1 42 33 74 01</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.le10h10.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.le10h10.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>COWORKSHOP</h2>\n<p>A design and modern space for nomads. We have hot drinks, snacks, call booths and Wifi (fiber) for you. You can also rent a meeting room.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>29-32, Rue des Vinaigriers, 75010 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 9 67 60 03 76</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.coworkshop.fr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.coworkshop.fr</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>La Mutinerie</h2>\n<p>Free together. La Mutinerie is a coworking space and a community of talents because coffee and meeting rooms are not enough to innovate.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>29 Rue de Meaux, 75019 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 9 81 14 92 00</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.mutinerie.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.mutinerie.org</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Anticafé</h2>\n<p>With us, you pay only the time, everything else is included: drinks, food, Wifi, meet, share, play, relax, work.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>6 Rue du Château d&#8217;Eau, 75010 Paris, France</li>\n<li>+33 1 42 80 17 57</li>\n<li><a href="https://www.anticafe.eu/">www.anticafe.eu</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Below the map of the partner coworking spaces:</strong></p>\n<div class="googlemaps"></div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/xPR6p2UIgmk" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/04/28/coworking-spaces-selection/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:84:"\n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		        \n		    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:115:"Sixth group of #WCEU speakers – Sarah Semark, Dmitry Mayorov, Michael Arestad, John Maeda, Morten Rand-Hendriksen";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpfr/~3/_Ho4MsoJHT8/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:151:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/04/27/sixth-group-of-wceu-speakers-sarah-semark-dmitry-mayorov-michael-arestad-john-maeda-morten-rand-hendriksen/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 27 Apr 2017 12:00:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:438:"\n		        Our sixth group of speakers are Sarah Semark, Dmitry Mayorov, Michael Arestad, John Maeda and Morten Rand-Hendriksen; and they will talk (among other things) about design topics. Please welcome them! Sarah Semark &#8211; Night of the living style guides Sarah Semark &#8230; Continue reading Sixth group of #WCEU speakers – Sarah Semark, Dmitry Mayorov, Michael Arestad, John Maeda, Morten Rand-Hendriksen  &#8594;		        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"WordCamp Europe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4763:"<div id="attachment_4938" style="width: 1410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="wp-image-4938 size-full" src="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/files/2017/04/sixth-group.jpg" alt="" width="1400" height="800" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Please welcome our next group of speakers – Sarah Semark, Dmitry Mayorov, Michael Arestad, John Maeda and Morten Rand-Hendriksen.</p></div>\n<p>Our sixth group of speakers are Sarah Semark, Dmitry Mayorov, Michael Arestad, John Maeda and Morten Rand-Hendriksen; and they will talk (among other things) about design topics. Please welcome them!</p>\n<p><span id="more-4913"></span></p>\n<h2>Sarah Semark &#8211; Night of the living style guides</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/sarah-semark/">Sarah Semark</a> is a designer, developer, and world-traveller. After running a business for eight years, she now works for Automattic designing and building WordPress themes. In her talk &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/night-of-the-living-style-guides/">Night of the living styleguides</a>&#8221; she will introduce us to styleguides for visualizing our work, making sure it stays consistent and answering the question &#8220;Why bother?&#8221;.</p>\n<h2>Dmitry Mayorov &#8211; New to theme design? Here&#8217;s what you should know.</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/dmitry-mayorov/">Dmitry</a> builds custom WordPress themes and plugins and runs a theme shop called ThemePatio where he creates simple and functional WordPress themes for bloggers, creatives, and business owners. You can make many mistakes starting off with theme design and Dmitry wants to help you with a good start in his talk &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/new-to-theme-design-heres-what-you-should-know">New to theme design? Here&#8217;s what you should know</a>&#8221;</p>\n<h2>Michael Arestad &#8211; Big design troubles in open source</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/michael-arestad/">Michael</a> is a designer at Automattic working on Jetpack and WordPress.com. He contributes to the WordPress project and is the most active on the design team. &#8220;What the heck can we do to improve the design process on open source projects?&#8221; asks Michael in his talk &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/big-design-troubles-in-open-source/">Big design troubles in open source</a>&#8221; and he will address the challenges including: communication difficulties, tech limitations, slow implementation times, community pushback, complex developer tools, unique design considerations, and lack of design process.</p>\n<h2>John Maeda &#8211; The three kinds of design</h2>\n<p>Global Head Computational Design and Inclusion of Automattic, <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/john-maeda/">John Maeda</a> is a formerly Partner at Kleiner Perkins Caufield &amp; Byers, President of Rhode Island School of Design and Professor at the MIT Media Laboratory. In &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/the-three-kinds-of-design/">The three kinds of design</a>&#8221; John will talk about how the old concept of bringing in a designer after everything is done to make it pretty is obsolete and how designers can improve this.</p>\n<h2>Morten Rand-Hendriksen &#8211; CSS Grid Changes Everything (about web layouts)</h2>\n<p><a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/speaker/morten-rand-hendriksen/">Morten Rand-Hendriksen</a> is a senior staff instructor at LinkedIn Learning and Lynda.com with 60+ courses published on WordPress, web standards, design and UX, and future technologies. He also teaches Interaction Design at Emily Carr University of Art and Design, and contributes to WordPress core and community projects. With CSS Grid now live in all major browsers you will learn in his talk &#8220;<a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/session/css-grid-changes-everything-about-web-layouts">CSS Grid Changes Everything (about web layouts)</a>&#8221; through examples, code snippets, and practical demos how to use CSS Grid in a theme for modern responsive layouts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Get your ticket today</h2>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already, don&#8217;t forget to get <a href="http://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/tickets/">your WordCamp Europe ticket</a>. Your WordCamp Europe ticket covers both days of the conference &#8211; June 16 and 17th &#8211; and contributor day on Thursday, June 15th. It grants you <strong>access to all sessions, lunch, coffee breaks, and the after party</strong>. It also includes an exclusive #WCEU 2017 <strong>t-shirt, stickers, and other great swag</strong>.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpfr/~4/_Ho4MsoJHT8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:151:"https://2017.europe.wordcamp.org/2017/04/27/sixth-group-of-wceu-speakers-sarah-semark-dmitry-mayorov-michael-arestad-john-maeda-morten-rand-hendriksen/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:52:"http://backend.userland.com/creativeCommonsRssModule";a:1:{s:7:"license";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/wpfr";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel";s:3:"hub";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:4:"info";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"uri";s:4:"wpfr";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";O:42:"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary":1:{s:7:"\0*\0data";a:11:{s:12:"content-type";s:23:"text/xml; charset=UTF-8";s:4:"etag";s:27:"OhvDTu1cI0WODSKZYt6E1AjMZ8w";s:13:"last-modified";s:29:"Wed, 03 May 2017 09:09:42 GMT";s:16:"content-encoding";s:4:"gzip";s:4:"date";s:29:"Wed, 03 May 2017 09:31:23 GMT";s:7:"expires";s:29:"Wed, 03 May 2017 09:31:23 GMT";s:13:"cache-control";s:18:"private, max-age=0";s:22:"x-content-type-options";s:7:"nosniff";s:16:"x-xss-protection";s:13:"1; mode=block";s:6:"server";s:3:"GSE";s:7:"alt-svc";s:37:"quic=":443"; ma=2592000; v="37,36,35"";}}s:5:"build";s:14:"20170331134305";}', 'no'),
